value.value: The temporal relation between the start of the process with respect to a reference process.
An orientation inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement at an angle.
An angle which is relatively high.
An angle which is relatively low.
An elongated raised margin or border.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's width being notably higher than its length.
Having a spindle-like shape that is wide in the middle and tapers at both ends.
Affecting all regions without specificity of distribution.
An affinity inhering in an anatomical structure by virtue of the bearer exhibiting a molecular interaction for acidic dyes under specific pH conditions.

definition.value: Eosin stains acidophilic structures, hence eosinophilic is the same as acidophilic.

value.value: Pertaining to the individual parts making up an aggregate fruit like a many-lobed "berry," such as a raspberry.

definition.value: Acinus is Latin for berry.

value.value: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being composed of or possessing inorganic material.
A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting of collagen.
A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being capable of swelling or stretching.
A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by narrow lines or grooves, usually parallel, that are oriented transversely relative to the long axis of the bearer.
A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having one or more nucleus.
A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting of keratin.
A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an open, latticed, or porous structure; used especially of bone.
A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking parts or having a reduced form compared to fully formed entities.
Cuspidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's possessing a single cusp.
A structural quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer consisting of multiple structures lacking any physical connection to each other.
A quality of a single cell inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.

definition.value: Use this term for morphologies that can *only* inhere in a cell, e.g. morphological qualities inhering in a cell by virtue of the presence, location or shape of one or more cell parts.

value.value: Absence due to a degenerative process.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the degree to which the bearers stands out or projects beyond a surface or line.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the extent to which the bearer is capable of being stretched or swollen.
Fibrosis is the formation of excess fibrous connective tissue in an organ or tissue in a reparative or reactive process.

definition.value: A width and length quality which is relatively small, where both width and length are decreased.

value.value: A broken quality where an entity is cracked or broken, usually a bone.
A fractured quality that is caused by a loss of bone mass (osteoporosis) that occurs as part of aging.
A fractured quality in which the fragment of bone tears away from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.
Existing or functioning as though broken into separate parts; disorganized; disunified.

definition.value: Moved to a child of wholeness because broken implies a trauma and fragmented could be caused by a developmental process. See HP:0100168 Fragmented epiphyses as an example.

value.value: Red due to increase blood circulation in a defined area.
A quality denoting the lack of a physical entity or object, such as a chemical.
A quality denoting the lack of an anatomical entity or cellular component.

definition.value: Absence of anatomical entity should only be used when all of the entity is absent. For example, absent teeth would mean all teeth are absent not some teeth are absent.

value.value: A quality inhering in a cell by virtue of the cell having a high nuclear/cytoplasmic ratio.

definition.value: A high nuclear/cytolasmic ratio is 70% or higher.
A rate which is relatively normal.
A quality of an object that has a value that is normal or average.
An acidity which is relatively normal.
A behavioural quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting normal or average activity.
A cellular motility which is normal or average.
A coiling which is normal or average.
A concentration which is relatively normal or average.
A contractility which is relatively normal or average.
A curvature which is relatively normal or average.
An elasticity which is relatively normal or average.
A flexibility which is relatively normal or average.
A fragility which is relatively normal or average.
A life span which is relatively normal or average.
A mass which is relatively normal or average.
A density which is relatively normal or average.
A mobility which is relatively normal or average.
